(firstQuint)Randomized Trial of Early Hemodynamic Management of Patients Following Acute Spinal Cord Injury.

 In this study, the investigators will learn about the effect of targeted blood pressure management (TPM) on participants healing from acute spinal cord injury.

 The investigators want to learn: The effect of two types of TPM on long term motor and sensory outcomes.

 The effect of two types of TPM on long-term pain and functional independence outcomes.

 How safe TPM is for participants.

